      "text": "ASOP's Fables.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 16.5,
      "end": 16.68,
      "text": "The Wolf.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 17.34,
      "end": 17.6,
      "text": "The Mother.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 18.34,
      "end": 18.88,
      "text": "Enter Child.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 20.42,
      "end": 23.56,
      "text": "A hungry wolf was prowling about in search of food.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 24.28,
      "end": 24.98,
      "text": "By and by.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 25.52,
      "end": 28.5,
      "text": "Attracted by the cries of a child, he came to a cottage.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 28.5,
      "end": 33.5,
      "text": "As he crouched beneath the window, he heard the Mother say to the child,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 34.04,
      "end": 37.52,
      "text": "stop crying do, or I'll throw you to the Wolf.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 38.14,
      "end": 43.42,
      "text": "Thinking she really meant what she said, he waited there a long time in the expectation",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 43.42,
      "end": 45.32,
      "text": "of satisfying his hunger.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 46.18,
      "end": 50.46,
      "text": "In the evening, he heard the Mother fondling her child and saying,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 51.26,
      "end": 56.26,
      "text": "if the naughty Wolf comes, he shan't get my little one, Daddy will kill him.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 56.26,
      "end": 60.32,
      "text": "The Wolf got up in much disgust and walked away.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 61.02,
      "end": 66.78,
      "text": "As for the people in that house, he said to himself, you can't believe a word they say.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 67.86,
      "end": 71.4,
      "text": "End of the Wolf, the Mother, enter Child.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
